<p>
For having been using <a href="https://www.gnome.org/">GNOME</a> for quite a long time, I was considering trying some tiling window managers to see what it&#39;s like a few weeks ago. Along the way, I found a nice window manager written in Python: <a href="http://www.qtile.org">Qtile</a>, what interests me most is that it&#39;s a <strong>hackable</strong> window manager, which makes it flexible to extend or change its behaviors.</p>
